	aFatherHeading={`A Father for the spiritually curious`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's something rarely said honestly from the religious side: you may have been right to walk away from what you were shown. A God who is mostly anger, a faith that's mostly rules, a community that wounds — those are worth rejecting. The question this Bible quietly raises is whether that picture was ever the real One.</p><p>Because underneath the religion, the institutions, and the people who got it wrong, the text itself keeps pointing to a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — not a scorekeeper, not a tyrant, not a list of conditions you have to meet first. One who, in the most famous story Jesus ever told, sees the child who left coming home from a long way off, and runs.</p><p>You don't have to believe that today. You don't have to believe anything to read. You're simply invited to look at the source for yourself, with all your doubt intact, and decide what's actually there. No one's keeping a record. No one's asking you to sign anything. The door is open, and there's no pressure on the other side of it.</p>`}
