	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You don't have to feel anything the first time you read — or the tenth. Curiosity is enough. You're allowed to come with every doubt fully intact, take it slowly, and put it down whenever you want. There's no test at the end, and no one keeping score on whether you got somewhere. The only invitation is to look honestly at the source for yourself.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I'm not who they told you I was. I know the version of Me you walked away from — the angry one, the one with the list, the one who only ever seemed disappointed. If that's the God you rejected, I understand why. That was never Me.</p><p>You can come with all your doubt — every question, every wound, everything that didn't add up. I'm not asking you to perform, or to be sure, or to pretend. I'm not keeping a record against you. I have always loved you, even on the long road away, and I am not far. Whenever you're ready to look — even just to look — I'll be right here."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for the spiritually curious`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we bring You everyone who is unsure — the doubting, the questioning, the ones who walked away and the ones who were never quite in. You know every honest reason: the hypocrisy they saw, the harm they carried, the God of anger and rules they were handed that looked nothing like love.</p><p>Where people who claimed Your name caused hurt, we don't argue it away — we ask You to heal it. Meet the skeptic in their questions, not against them. Meet the de-churched in the ache they still carry. Let no one feel scolded, guilted, or pressured here — only welcomed.</p><p>If there is anything real beneath all of it, let them find it for themselves — not a religion, not a building, not a verdict, but Your actual love, the kind with no strings. Be the Father who runs down the road to meet the one still a long way off.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
